headlines.description: Cristiano Ronaldo converted two penalties as he scored for the ninth Serie A game in a row to give Juventus a flattering 3-0 win over Fiorentina.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ronaldo continues scoring run as Juve stay top

headlines.description: AC Milan, missing Zlatan Ibrahimovic with a bout of flu, were held 1-1 by Verona as Daniel Maldini, the son of Paolo Maldini, made his debut.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maldini makes Milan debut in disappointing draw

headlines.description: Ciro Immobile and Felipe Caicedo both scored twice as a rampant Lazio thrashed SPAL 5-1 on Sunday to maintain their Serie A title challenge.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lazio thrash SPAL to keep up pressure on Inter

venue.fullName: Stadio Ettore Giardiniero - Via del Mare

venue.displayName: Stadio Ettore Giardiniero - Via del Mare

headlines.description: Romelu Lukaku scored a quickfire second-half double to give Inter Milan a 2-0 win at Udinese on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lukaku's double ends Inter's run of draws
